New Records: Domantas Sabonis had a career-high 28 rebounds.
It was Sabonis’ 33rd double-double of the season and 24th game of his career with 20 or more rebounds.
The NBA’s previous high for rebounds in a game this season was 23 by San Antonio's Victor Wembanyama.
Key Match Events: Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and a career-high 28 rebounds.
The Sacramento Kings used a fourth quarter rally to beat the Boston Celtics 114-97.
The victory extended Sacramento's season-high win streak to six games.
